{
  "texts": [
    "Volume represents the initial size and amount of data collected, while velocity refers to the data generation rate.",
    "Variety refers to data diversity, with challenges in variety such as data standardization.",
    "Veracity refers to data quality and accuracy, while value refers to the activities companies can perform with the collected data.The value of big data technology increases significantly when well implemented within production systems, allowing companies to better customize products and achieve high levels of satisfaction [75].",
    "However, it presents challenges such as data protection, relevant data identification, and cleaning techniques for analyzing data with different formats.",
    "Data mining is a process that analyzes hidden patterns of data from different perspectives to obtain useful information [76]."
  ]
}